      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are music royalties considered passive income?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, once the initial work of composing and recording is complete, the ongoing royalties generated by the music—whether played on the radio, streamed online, or used in a film—are considered a form of passive income."
